{
  "number": 967,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/967",
  "title": "[Docs] While developing the assets are generated in /js build we load them from /assets/",
  "body": "Kind of misunderstanding with `jekyll-assets` probably.\n\nReproduction case:\n- `npm run dev:docs`\n- edit `search.js` file and save\n- the livereload says `js/search.js updated`\n- the page includes `/assets/search.js` through the `{{ js search.js }}` directive, so you will always reach the old version of the file, generated at startup time... (struggled 15min on it without understanding what was happening....)\n\nQuick fix:\n\n``` html\n<script src=\"{{ \"/js/search.js\" | prepend: site.baseurl }}\"></script>\n```\n\ninstead of\n\n```\n{{ js search.js }}\n```\n",
